---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout 
  title="Balayage" 
  price="$230" 
  duration="3-4 hours"
  image="/images/optimized/color-transformation_800.webp"
>
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Hand-Painted Highlights for Effortless Beauty</h2>
  
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
    Balayage is the art of creating sun-kissed, natural-looking highlights through a freehand painting technique. This French coloring method has revolutionized the hair industry by delivering gorgeous, low-maintenance color that grows out beautifully. Experience the ultimate in customized color with results that look like you've spent months in the sun.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Art of Balayage</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
    Unlike traditional foil highlights, balayage involves hand-painting color directly onto hair sections, creating a graduated, natural effect. The technique allows for complete customization – from subtle, barely-there highlights to bold, high-contrast dimensions. The result is a lived-in color that requires minimal maintenance while delivering maximum impact.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Why Choose Balayage?</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li>Natural, sun-kissed results that mimic nature</li>
    <li>Soft, seamless grow-out with no harsh lines</li>
    <li>Low maintenance – touch-ups needed only 3-4 times per year</li>
    <li>Completely customizable placement and intensity</li>
    <li>Works with all hair colors and textures</li>
    <li>Creates multi-dimensional color and movement</li>
    <li>Less damaging than traditional highlights</li>
    <li>Perfect for the modern, busy lifestyle</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Balayage Variations</h3>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
    <div class="bg-[#F8F9FA] rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Classic Balayage</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Traditional sun-kissed highlights with natural placement</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-[#F8F9FA] rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Ombré Balayage</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Graduated color from dark roots to light ends</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-[#F8F9FA] rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Sombré</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Subtle version with softer transitions</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-[#F8F9FA] rounded-lg p-4">
      <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Face-Framing</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Concentrated brightness around the face</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Balayage Process</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li>Detailed consultation to design your custom look</li>
    <li>Hair sectioning based on desired placement</li>
    <li>Custom color mixing for your perfect shade</li>
    <li>Freehand painting of lightener onto selected sections</li>
    <li>Strategic placement for natural sun-kissed effect</li>
    <li>Processing in open air for soft transitions</li>
    <li>Toning to achieve desired warmth or coolness</li>
    <li>Deep conditioning treatment for shine</li>
    <li>Professional styling to showcase dimension</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Perfect For Every Hair Type</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
    Balayage works beautifully on all hair types and colors:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li><strong>Brunettes:</strong> Caramel, honey, and golden tones add warmth</li>
    <li><strong>Blondes:</strong> Platinum and champagne create luminous effects</li>
    <li><strong>Redheads:</strong> Copper and strawberry enhance natural warmth</li>
    <li><strong>Black hair:</strong> Subtle bronze or bold contrasts possible</li>
    <li><strong>Curly hair:</strong> Enhances natural texture and movement</li>
    <li><strong>Fine hair:</strong> Creates illusion of thickness and dimension</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Low-Maintenance Advantage</h3>
  <div class="bg-[#FFDEE2] bg-opacity-20 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
    <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3">Maintenance Timeline:</h4>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
      <li>First touch-up: 3-4 months</li>
      <li>Toner refresh: Every 6-8 weeks if desired</li>
      <li>Full balayage refresh: 2-3 times per year</li>
      <li>Use purple shampoo weekly for blonde tones</li>
      <li>Deep condition bi-weekly for optimal health</li>
      <li>Protect from sun and chlorine exposure</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
      The beauty of balayage is its grow-out – there's no harsh line, so you can go longer between appointments!
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Styling Your Balayage</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
    Balayage looks stunning styled in various ways:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
    <li>Beach waves showcase the dimension perfectly</li>
    <li>Sleek straight styles display color gradation</li>
    <li>Updos reveal hidden pops of color</li>
    <li>Braids create beautiful woven color effects</li>
    <li>Air-dried texture enhances the natural look</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-[#D3E4FD] bg-opacity-20 rounded-lg p-6">
    <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
      "Balayage isn't just a hair color technique – it's a lifestyle choice. It's for the woman who wants to look effortlessly beautiful, who values her time, and who believes that the best color is the one that looks like it was kissed by the sun itself."
    </p>
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>